abstract: The car rental company says that neither Hertz nor anyone else made a takeover offer by a Monday deadline that satisfied its conditions.
snippet: The car rental company says that neither Hertz nor anyone else made a takeover offer by a Monday deadline that satisfied its conditions.
lead_paragraph: The Dollar Thrifty Automotive Group said on Tuesday that neither Hertz Global Holdings nor anyone else had submitted a buyout offer that met its conditions by a Monday deadline, and the company said it was no longer pursuing a sale.

headline.main: Dollar Thrifty Takes Itself Off the Market
